{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/math-correctness/2026-06-07-power-of-two-test-masking.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"math-correctness","title":"Power-of-two-only test inputs hide padding/truncation bugs in signal & transform code","date":"2026-06-07","tags":["signal-processing","fft","wavelet","testing","adversarial-review","edge-cases","catalog-skills"],"symptom":"New spectrogram + wavelet_denoise skills passed all unit tests and ran end-to-end, but an adversarial review found they silently produce wrong results for non-power-of-two inputs. Every test happened to use a power-of-two size.","root_cause":"ix-signal's rfft zero-pads each frame to the next power of two, and the Haar DWT halves length per level (dropping the last sample of an odd block). Both behaviors are invisible when every test input is already a power of two / divisible by 2^levels.","path":"docs/solutions/math-correctness/2026-06-07-power-of-two-test-masking.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/math-correctness/2026-06-08-inharmonicity-estimator-pitch-error-confound.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"math-correctness","title":"Measuring guitar inharmonicity — fixed-f0 fit is corrupted by pitch error; the engine is not \"too harmonic\"","date":"2026-06-08","tags":["acoustic-tune","inharmonicity","dsp","oracle","guitar-engine","negative-result","estimator"],"path":"docs/solutions/math-correctness/2026-06-08-inharmonicity-estimator-pitch-error-confound.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/math-correctness/jacobi-vs-power-iteration-repeated-eigenvalues.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"math-correctness","title":"Jacobi vs power iteration for matrices with repeated eigenvalues","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["eigenvalue","jacobi","power-iteration","linear-algebra","deflation"],"symptom":"Classical MDS of a unit square returned pairwise-distance error 1.14 instead of 1e-6; LDA with axis-aligned class clusters produced duplicated or wrong discriminants","root_cause":"Power iteration + rank-1 deflation converges to an arbitrary vector in the dominant eigenspace when eigenvalues are repeated. Deflation then only removes one direction of a multi-dimensional eigenspace, leaving residual that poisons subsequent iterations.","path":"docs/solutions/math-correctness/jacobi-vs-power-iteration-repeated-eigenvalues.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/math-correctness/lda-non-symmetric-deflation.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"math-correctness","title":"LDA non-symmetric deflation produces duplicated or wrong discriminants","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["lda","eigenvalue","generalized-eigenvalue","deflation","symmetrization"],"symptom":"LDA with three axis-aligned class clusters returned duplicated components; the second explained value collapsed to near zero","root_cause":"Naive LDA formulation forms M = S_W^-1 S_B which is NOT symmetric, then uses rank-1 symmetric deflation M -= lambda v v^T which is only valid for Hermitian matrices","path":"docs/solutions/math-correctness/lda-non-symmetric-deflation.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/math-correctness/sedenion-log-negative-reals.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"math-correctness","title":"Sedenion log(-1) principal value needs pi on an imaginary axis","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["sedenion","hypercomplex","logarithm","principal-value","quaternion-limit"],"symptom":"exp(log(-1)) returned 1 instead of -1, breaking round-trip for negative real sedenions","root_cause":"Scalar+vector decomposition of log assumed non-zero vector part; for pure-real negative inputs it collapsed to ln(|s|) alone with no angle component","path":"docs/solutions/math-correctness/sedenion-log-negative-reals.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/test-failures/kernel-pca-symmetric-centroid-trap.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"test-failures","title":"Kernel PCA test assertion fails on symmetric input — centroids collapse to zero","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["kernel-pca","test-design","symmetry","centroid"],"symptom":"Test asserting that Kernel PCA separates 'inner ring from outer ring' failed because both rings had mean projection ~0","root_cause":"Both rings were centered at the origin. PCA projections of symmetric point clouds have centroids at the origin in ALL components, regardless of which kernel is used","path":"docs/solutions/test-failures/kernel-pca-symmetric-centroid-trap.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/2026-06-07-dogfood-yield-before-after-measurement.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"workflow-patterns","title":"Measuring a yield improvement from an append-only ledger (the cumulative-blend trap)","date":"2026-06-07","tags":["thinking-machine","dogfood","telemetry","hits-jsonl","measurement","before-after","xargs-race"],"symptom":"After shipping catalog + data-binding fixes, `ix pipeline hits` reported yield_rate 0.43 — looked like a weak gain, but the real post-fix yield was 0.66. The aggregate blended pre-fix and post-fix runs.","root_cause":"hits.jsonl is an append-only cumulative ledger; the `hits` aggregator averages ALL entries since the file began, so a large pre-fix tail drags the mean down and hides the post-fix delta. A parallel `xargs -P` batch harness also corrupted the raw results (append race).","path":"docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/2026-06-07-dogfood-yield-before-after-measurement.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/multi-ai-review-before-merge.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"workflow-patterns","title":"Multi-AI review should happen BEFORE merge, not after","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["code-review","multi-ai","octopus","workflow","merge-before-review"],"symptom":"Session dispatched 6 parallel agents -> merged their work -> then ran multi-AI review and found 10 issues, all already committed","root_cause":"Review is cheap to run on isolated worktrees but expensive to apply as follow-up commits after merge; flow should have reviewed-then-merged, not merged-then-reviewed","path":"docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/multi-ai-review-before-merge.md"}
{"schema_version":"0.1.0","id":"ix:docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/parallel-worktree-merge-pitfalls.md","repo":"ix","kind":"solution","category":"workflow-patterns","title":"Parallel worktree merge pitfalls when agents write to main","date":"2026-04-09","tags":["git","worktree","parallel-agents","orchestration","team-of-teams"],"symptom":"Parallel worker agents return as 'completed' but shared files conflict and some agents write to main instead of their isolated worktree","root_cause":"Worker agents use cargo and shared target/ directories, don't commit on return, and can accidentally resolve paths to the main working tree","path":"docs/solutions/workflow-patterns/parallel-worktree-merge-pitfalls.md"}
